HEADWORD: Physemaria
<hw>Phys`e*ma"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <grk>fy^shma</grk> a blowing.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
group of simple marine organisms, usually classed as the lowest of the
sponges. They have inflated hollow bodies.</def>⟦br⟧
